IDEO DISC FOR THE STORAGE OF OFFICE DOCUMENTS AND ENGINEERING GRAPHICS.     A DESCRIPTION OF THE OPTICAL DATA DISC, A MEANS OF CONVERTING HUMAN-READABLEDOCUMENTATION TO HIGH-DENSITY STORAGE ON PHOTO SENSITIVE MATERIALS, IS GIVEN,WITH DETAILS OF ITS DIMENSIONS AND MANUFACTURERS. ATTRIBUTES OF THE OPTICALDATA DISC, INCLUDING DATA ENTRY, CODE FORMAT, REPLICATION AND PROJECTED COSTOF BLANK DISCS, ARE OUTLINED. A COMPARISON OF OPTICAL DATA DISCS ANDMICROFORMS IS MADE, WITH REFERENCE TO STORAGE CAPACITY, MATERIAL COST ANDRETRIEVAL TIME. THE FUTURE AVAILABILITY OF THE DISC IS ASSESSED